Overcrowding and safety violations caused

an aging ferry to capsize in the Ganges River, killing as many as 400 people, a government report said.
About 200 people were on the upper deck, he said.
"We are trying our best, but because of the current, we are not able to go near the launch," Pathak said.
Only then will we be able to get the bodies out," Singh said.
The ferry was designed to carry about 160 people, but was was always overcrowded, he said.
Jetty workers, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said 535 tickets were sold for the trip.
"Police are trying to control the crowds and console them," he said.
